text.section:
If a person is involuntarily admitted by a court order, the person shall be transported to the ICF/ID designated by the cabinet and accompanied by the following documents:
A copy of the petition for involuntary admission;
The certificate of qualified professionals in the area of intellectual disabilities;
A current physical examination that documents no serious medical issues;
The psychological examination or assessment that documents a Full Scale IQ in the moderate to severe range of intellectual disability; and
The order of involuntary admission.
